%%prun
# Set up projections
p_ll = pyproj.Proj(init='epsg:4326')
p_mt = pyproj.Proj("+proj=eqdc +lat_0=39 +lon_0=-96 +lat_1=33 +lat_2=45 +x_0=0 +y_0=0 +datum=NAD83 +units=m +no_defs") #USA
# p_mt=pyproj.Proj("+proj=eqdc +lat_0=30 +lon_0=10 +lat_1=43 +lat_2=62 +x_0=0 +y_0=0 +ellps=intl +units=m +no_defs") #PL

#p_ll = pyproj.Proj(init='epsg:3857')
#p_mt = pyproj.Proj(init='epsg:4087') # metric; same as EPSG:900913 3857
#p_mt = pyproj.Proj(init='epsg:4979')
#p_mt = pyproj.Proj(init='esri:102031')

# Create corners of rectangle to be transformed to a grid
#nw = shapely.geometry.Point((-5.0, 40.0))
#se = shapely.geometry.Point((-4.0, 41.0))

#nw = shapely.geometry.Point((55.053571, 13.709483))
#se = shapely.geometry.Point((48.802844, 24.225555))

#ws = shapely.geometry.Point((13.709483, 48.802844)) ok
#en = shapely.geometry.Point((24.225555, 55.053571)) ok

# sw = shapely.geometry.Point((48.555900, 10.846370)) #PL
# ne = shapely.geometry.Point((54.821838, 26.158234)) #PL

# sw = shapely.geometry.Point((24.873196,-126.613141)) #USA
# ne = shapely.geometry.Point((41.921174, -103.527889)) #USA

sw = shapely.geometry.Point((32.731125, -116.944403)) #USA SMALL
ne = shapely.geometry.Point((41.921174, -103.527889)) #USA SMALL

# sw = shapely.geometry.Point((21.999586, -158.231030))
# ne = shapely.geometry.Point((72.568437, 175.755116))

#ws = shapely.geometry.Point((13.709483, 55.053571))
#en = shapely.geometry.Point((24.225555, 48.802844))

stepsize = 100000 # 50 km grid step size

# Project corners to target projection
s = pyproj.transform(p_ll, p_mt, sw.y, sw.x) # Transform NW point to 3857
e = pyproj.transform(p_ll, p_mt, ne.y, ne.x) # .. same for SE

# Iterate over 2D area
gridpoints = []
x = s[0]
while x < e[0]:
    y = s[1]
    while y < e[1]:
        p = shapely.geometry.Point(pyproj.transform(p_mt, p_ll, x, y))
        gridpoints.append(p)
        y += stepsize
    x += stepsize

with open(r'C:\Users\Zdzich\Desktop\GRID WORKING\output\testout4.csv', 'w') as of:
    of.write('lat,lon\n')
    for p in gridpoints:
        of.write('{:f},{:f}\n'.format(p.y, p.x))
        
print("Finished")

def nearest(row, geom_union, df1, df2, geom1_col='geometry', geom2_col='geometry', src_column=None):
    """Find the nearest point and return the corresponding value from specified column."""
    # Find the geometry that is closest
    nearest = df2[geom2_col] == nearest_points(row[geom1_col], geom_union)[1]
    # Get the corresponding value from df2 (matching is based on the geometry)
    value = df2[nearest][src_column].get_values()[int(0)]
    print('Found')
    return value

# Shoe-horn existing data for entry into KDTree routines

def do_kdtree(points_list,array_grid):
    mytree = scipy.spatial.cKDTree(array_grid)
    dist, indexes = mytree.query(points_list)
    return indexes
